The paper deals with the complexity of nondeterministic unitary OBDDs, which is a topic related to computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of Boolean functions, which falls under the scope of cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). The use of strong 1-fooling sets and width hierarchy suggests a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Lastly, the paper's focus on unitary operations and quantum logic implies a possible connection to cs.QLI (Quantum Physics).
